
[1]convex

   CONVEX, a. [L.] Rising or swelling on the exterior surface into a
   spherical or round form; gibbous; opposed to concave, which expresses a
   round form of the interior surface; as a convex mirror or lens.

   CONVEX, n. A convex body; as heavens convex.
